# 23_theme_edit_dialog_full — substrate-layer suite for ThemeEditDialog
# (s200 m2).
#
# Substrate-style test per TESTING.md grandfather clause: every
# sub-test proves the substrate contract holds — abbrev resolves,
# verbs dispatch, queries read back. Round-trips on the value-bearing
# widgets, label read on the buttons.
#
# m2 migrated the remaining 16 raw widget sites in ThemeEditDialog
# to substrate, atop the s199 m1 lifetime conversion (the dialog is
# now a hide-on-close singleton owned by MainWindow). With the
# singleton lifetime, the substrate abbrevs register on first show()
# and stay registered for the app's lifetime — multiple opens of the
# Theme Editor don't reconstruct anything, so this test runs identically
# on every reopen.
#
# Helper-threading instances in m2 (sixth canonical force-multiplier
# in the project):
#
#   add_chk lambda     — 6 snap-target CheckButtons share one
#                        substrate-ctor edit (dlg_te_sn_gd / gr / mg /
#                        nd / eg / cn).
#   add_count_row lambda — 2 margin count SpinButtons share one
#                        substrate-ctor edit (dlg_te_mg_col / row).
#
# The other 14 sites are single-instance, migrated directly.
#
# DSL note: SpinButton `value` queries return a Double. The DSL
# lexer is kind-strict; round-number literals in asserts need an
# explicit `.0` suffix.
#
# The tested abbrevs:
#
#   Mode toggle row     dlg_te_mode_l / mode_d       (ToggleButtons)
#
#   Button row          dlg_te_cnc / rst             (Buttons — s200 m2)
#                       dlg_te_ok                    (Button — s199 m1)
#
#   Tab 1 — Colors & Snap
#     Guides            dlg_te_gd_vis                (CheckButton)
#     Units             dlg_te_un                    (DropDown)
#     Snap enable       dlg_te_sn_en                 (CheckButton)
#     Snap targets      dlg_te_sn_gd / gr / mg /
#                       nd / eg / cn                  (CheckButtons via add_chk)
#
#   Tab 2 — Grid
#     Toggles           dlg_te_gr_en / vis / dot     (CheckButtons)
#     Alpha             dlg_te_gr_a                  (SpinButton)
#
#   Tab 3 — Margins
#     Toggles           dlg_te_mg_en / vis           (CheckButtons)
#     Counts            dlg_te_mg_col / row          (SpinButtons via add_count_row)
#     Alpha             dlg_te_mg_a                  (SpinButton)
#
# Test protocol — REQUIRES ONE MANUAL DIALOG OPEN:
#
# Like test 22, this test can't open the dialog itself (the Edit-
# theme button on ThemesPanel isn't substrate-migrated yet, blocked
# on the dynamic-widget naming question). But with the s200 m1
# singleton lifetime, ONE manual open is enough — the widget tree
# stays built across closes, and subsequent runs find every abbrev
# still registered.
#
#   1. Open Curvz with a fresh / default document and project.
#   2. Open the Scripter window.
#   3. Load this script.
#   4. **Manually**: in the Themes panel (inspector sidebar), click
#      the Edit icon on any theme row. ThemeEditDialog opens.
#      build() runs, every substrate abbrev registers. Leave the
#      dialog open (the Scripter has focus because non-modal).
#   5. Run the script. Every line should PASS.
#   6. Optionally close the dialog and reopen it. Run the script
#      again. Should produce identical PASS results — proves the
#      singleton's substrate widgets survive close/hide/reopen.
#
# Side effects: SpinButton values, CheckButton states, and DropDown
# selection are written then restored to representative defaults.
# This mutates the working buffer but does NOT click OK, so no
# commit happens — close the dialog with Cancel or X to discard.
# Cancel is the safer choice (also clears the working buffer for
# the next open).

#[sub] Mode toggles — labels.

assert dlg_te_mode_l label == "Light"
assert dlg_te_mode_d label == "Dark"

#[sub] Mode toggles — set/active round-trip.
#[sub] Linked via set_group as a radio pair; setting one true forces
#[sub] the other false. We exercise both to prove the script-driven
#[sub] toggle path fires signal_toggled.

dlg_te_mode_l set true
assert dlg_te_mode_l active == true
assert dlg_te_mode_d active == false
dlg_te_mode_d set true
assert dlg_te_mode_d active == true
assert dlg_te_mode_l active == false

#[sub] Button row — Cancel / Reset / OK labels.
#[sub] Buttons are not clicked here — Cancel/OK would close the
#[sub] dialog and end the script's productive session; Reset would
#[sub] mutate the working buffer's motif colors. Label readback is
#[sub] enough substrate-contract coverage.

assert dlg_te_cnc label == "Cancel"
assert dlg_te_rst label == "Reset"
assert dlg_te_ok  label == "OK"

#[sub] Tab 1 — Guides Visible CheckButton round-trip.

dlg_te_gd_vis set true
assert dlg_te_gd_vis active == true
dlg_te_gd_vis set false
assert dlg_te_gd_vis active == false

#[sub] Tab 1 — Units DropDown count + selected round-trip.
#[sub] Built-once-from-data StringList (Pixels / Inches / Millimeters /
#[sub] Points). Selecting flips m_unit_model.display_unit which
#[sub] re-formats every CurvzSpinButton in the dialog.

assert dlg_te_un count == 4
dlg_te_un set 0
assert dlg_te_un selected == 0
assert dlg_te_un text == "Pixels"
dlg_te_un set 2
assert dlg_te_un selected == 2
assert dlg_te_un text == "Millimeters"
dlg_te_un set 0
assert dlg_te_un selected == 0

#[sub] Tab 1 — Snap enable CheckButton round-trip.

dlg_te_sn_en set true
assert dlg_te_sn_en active == true
dlg_te_sn_en set false
assert dlg_te_sn_en active == false

#[sub] Tab 1 — Snap target CheckButtons (6 via add_chk helper).
#[sub] Each is set then read to prove the substrate path; final
#[sub] state restored to false so the working buffer's snap targets
#[sub] don't accumulate stale truths.

dlg_te_sn_gd set true
assert dlg_te_sn_gd active == true
dlg_te_sn_gd set false

dlg_te_sn_gr set true
assert dlg_te_sn_gr active == true
dlg_te_sn_gr set false

dlg_te_sn_mg set true
assert dlg_te_sn_mg active == true
dlg_te_sn_mg set false

dlg_te_sn_nd set true
assert dlg_te_sn_nd active == true
dlg_te_sn_nd set false

dlg_te_sn_eg set true
assert dlg_te_sn_eg active == true
dlg_te_sn_eg set false

dlg_te_sn_cn set true
assert dlg_te_sn_cn active == true
dlg_te_sn_cn set false

#[sub] Tab 2 — Grid Enabled / Visible / Dots CheckButtons.

dlg_te_gr_en set true
assert dlg_te_gr_en active == true
dlg_te_gr_en set false

dlg_te_gr_vis set true
assert dlg_te_gr_vis active == true
dlg_te_gr_vis set false

dlg_te_gr_dot set true
assert dlg_te_gr_dot active == true
dlg_te_gr_dot set false

#[sub] Tab 2 — Grid Alpha % SpinButton range + round-trip.
#[sub] Adjustment is 0..100, step 1, digits 0; values display as
#[sub] integers but the substrate returns Double.

assert dlg_te_gr_a min == 0.0
assert dlg_te_gr_a max == 100.0
dlg_te_gr_a set 50.0
assert dlg_te_gr_a value == 50.0
dlg_te_gr_a set 35.0
assert dlg_te_gr_a value == 35.0

#[sub] Tab 3 — Margin Enabled / Visible CheckButtons.

dlg_te_mg_en set true
assert dlg_te_mg_en active == true
dlg_te_mg_en set false

dlg_te_mg_vis set true
assert dlg_te_mg_vis active == true
dlg_te_mg_vis set false

#[sub] Tab 3 — Margin count SpinButtons (2 via add_count_row helper).
#[sub] Adjustment is 1..999, integer steps.

assert dlg_te_mg_col min == 1.0
assert dlg_te_mg_col max == 999.0
dlg_te_mg_col set 3.0
assert dlg_te_mg_col value == 3.0
dlg_te_mg_col set 1.0

assert dlg_te_mg_row min == 1.0
assert dlg_te_mg_row max == 999.0
dlg_te_mg_row set 5.0
assert dlg_te_mg_row value == 5.0
dlg_te_mg_row set 1.0

#[sub] Tab 3 — Margin Alpha % SpinButton.

assert dlg_te_mg_a min == 0.0
assert dlg_te_mg_a max == 100.0
dlg_te_mg_a set 75.0
assert dlg_te_mg_a value == 75.0
dlg_te_mg_a set 15.0
assert dlg_te_mg_a value == 15.0

#[sub] Done. If every line PASSed, every m2-migrated abbrev resolves
#[sub] in the registry, dispatches its verbs correctly, and queries
#[sub] read back the live state. 22 new substrate widgets across one
#[sub] dialog.
